arts.ttl: Lille extends unbeaten run to 18 games after draw with lowly Nantes in Ligue 1
arts.sum: Elsewhere, Augustine Boakye got his first goals for Saint-Etienne and new Norwegian coach Eirik Horneland celebrated his first game in charge of the club in a 3-1 win against Reims. Boakye, a midfielder from Ghana, struck twice in the second half as Saint-Etienne snapped a run of three league defeats and moved up to 14th place.
